      <div class="article-teaser">
        The TfL Safety and Citizenship team have experience in adapting our presentations for faith schools. We can run sessions without videos, or entirely through question-and-answer and role play.
        
      </div>
    
    <div class="on-this-page">
      
      
           
      <div>

<p>We will make every effort to adapt our presentation for your pupils and are happy to arrive early, or arrange a meeting in advance of your booking to show teachers presentation materials and discuss suitable content.</p>

<p>Presentations last about an hour. We would typically talk about:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Getting help</li>
	<li>Using the <a href="/fares/free-and-discounted-travel">Zip Oyster photocard</a> correctly</li>
	<li>Using buses</li>
	<li>Using the Underground</li>
	<li>Active travel choices</li>
	<li>Personal safety when travelling</li>
</ul>

<p>As part of our Hackney Junior Citizenship Scheme, we run four days exclusively for Orthodox Jewish schools to make the scheme more accessible for the local Jewish community.</p>

<p>If you are a school in Hackney that would be interested in attending one of these dedicated days, or if you would just like to discuss our presentations, then please call on 020 7565 7303 or email <a href="mailto:tflsafetyandcitizenship&#64;ltmuseum.co.uk">tflsafetyandcitizenship&#64;ltmuseum.co.uk</a>.</p>
</div>
 
      
        
          
